New year, same crew 👯‍♂️ 

My biggest health tip as we head into the new year is to make small changes - day after day, week after week. You don’t need to reinvent the wheel and do a full overhaul. It takes  over 2 months for a habit to become automatic- make little changes. Start with diet. Then 2 weeks later increase movement, so on and so forth … 

The biggest things that help ME stay fit as a mom of 3 who just hit 40: 

💪🏼 move everyday. It doesn’t have to be at the gym. My goal is 15k everyday, but 10k is a great goal too. 

💪🏼 track what you eat. You’d be surprised at how little/much you eat! 

💪🏼Weight train: pick up the weights! As we get older we lose muscle mass. Strength training is so important for many reasons including increasing your metabolism, being strong, and having a lean look. 

💪🏼 surround yourself with positive people who lift you up! So grateful to be back with my crew at @tailored_fitness_buffalo! After a few months off with an injury I’m excited to see where this year takes me 🙌🏼

Buffalo gals…if you’re looking for a new home in the 716, this is your spot.

You can respect & love your body but STILL WANT MORE FOR YOURSELF 👏🏼 I love the movement of giving yourself grace and loving your body through every stage of your life… but don’t let anyone ever shame you for putting yourself first or wanting more for yourself - your nutrition, your workouts, and your mental health 👏🏼

I am a person who struggles without routine, so once summer was over I was ready for a refresh. I enjoyed myself but I was feeling sluggish and not myself. 

Here are some things I changed to lean out. I lost about 10 lbs and TONS of inches. I don’t care as much about the weight, more about feeling good about myself and being strong/ lean. 

1. 15k steps per day no matter what. This meant sometimes at 9 pm I’d be doing emails or working on tiktok on the treadmill. 

2. Intermittent fasting: I normally do this but I was more consistent with it fasting from about 9 pm- 11 am or so the next day. I feel so much better when I do this. 

3. Diet: Cleaned up my diet and focused on lean protein and healthy fats. Still eat carbs but good sources like fruit and  brown rice. 

4. Strength training: continued strength training 3x per week. 

5. Cardio: increased my cardio to 3 runs per week. 

6. Water, water, water. 

Ironically, I wasn’t able to run/ lift for 7 weeks during October and November so I got these results NOT EVEN WORKING OUT. 

So.. I’m here to say you can do it if you want to. It’ll take lots of dedication, hard work, perseverance, and discipline… but if you want it.. you can do it. 🤍
